  "paths": {
    "/v1/users": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "Operations on Users"
        ],
        "summary": "List / search all Users.",
        "description": "<p>List / search through all Users. This API call is only available for admin users. This API endpoint uses the OData query language as described in this Microsoft API guidelines document for <a href=\"https://github.com/layeredprints/api-guidelines/blob/vNext/Guidelines.md#97-filtering\">filtering</a>, <a href= \"https://github.com/layeredprints/api-guidelines/blob/vNext/Guidelines.md#98-pagination\">pagination</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/layeredprints/api-guidelines/blob/vNext/Guidelines.md#96-sorting-collections\">sorting</a>.<br><br>There are several Nodejs libraries available providing these query operations out of the box (eg: <a href=\"https://github.com/TossShinHwa/node-odata\">https://github.com/TossShinHwa/node-odata</a>)</p> <br>",
        "operationId": "listUsersUsingGet",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": null,
            "$ref": "#/components/parameters/Authorization"
          },
          {
            "name": "$filter",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "<p>The filter querystring parameter allows clients to filter a collection of resources that are addressed by a request URL. The expression specified with filter is evaluated for each resource in the collection, and only items where the expression evaluates to true are included in the response. Resources for which the expression evaluates to false or to null, or which reference properties that are unavailable due to permissions, are omitted from the response.<br /><br /></p> <p>Example return all users with role equal to gamer<br /><br /></p> <pre><code>GET /v1/users?filter=role eq gamer</code></pre><br /><br /> <p>The value of the filter option is a Boolean expression.<br /><br /></p> <p>Services that support filter SHOULD support the following minimal set of operations.<br /><br /></p> <table>\n  <tr><td>Comparison operators</td><td></td><td></td></tr>\n  <tr><td>eq</td><td>Equal</td><td>subject eq 'Redmond'</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>ne</td><td>Not equal</td><td>city ne 'London'</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>gt</td><td>Greater than</td><td>price gt 10</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>ge</td><td>Greater than or equal</td><td>price ge 20</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>lt</td><td>Less than</td><td>price lt 10</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>le</td><td>Less than or equal</td><td>price le 20</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>Logical operators</td><td></td><td></td></tr>\n  <tr><td>and</td><td>Logical and</td><td>price le 200 and price gt 3.5</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>or</td><td>Logical or</td><td>price le 3.5 or price gt 200</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>not</td><td>Logical negation</td><td>not price le 3.5</td></tr>\n  <tr><td>Grouping operators</td><td></td><td></td></tr>\n  <tr><td>( )</td><td>Precedence grouping</td><td>(priority eq 1 or city eq 'Redmond') and price gt 100</td></tr>\n</table>",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "$top",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "<p>Clients MAY use $top and $skip query parameters to specify a number of results to return and an offset into the collection. When both $top and $skip are given by a client, the server SHOULD first apply $skip and then $top on the collection.</p> <pre><code>GET /v1/users?$top=5&skip=2</code></pre>",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "$skip",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "$orderBy",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "<p>The value of the orderBy parameter contains a comma-separated list of expressions used to sort the items. <br /><br /></p> <p>The expression MAY include the suffix \"asc\" for ascending or \"desc\" for descending, separated from the property name by one or more spaces. If \"asc\" or \"desc\" is not specified, the service MUST order by the specified property in ascending order.<br /><br /></p> <p>Items MUST be sorted by the result values of the first expression, and then items with the same value for the first expression are sorted by the result value of the second expression, and so on. The sort order is the inherent order for the type of the property.<br /><br /></p> <p>Example: return all users sorted by email in ascending order<br /><br /></p> <pre><code>GET /v1/users?orderBy=email asc</code></pre>",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "$select",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            },
            "description": "A data service URI with a $select query option identifies the same set of Entries as a URI without a $select query option; however, the value of $select specifies that the response body should only include a subset of the properties which would have been returned had the URI not included a $select query option. <p>Example: retrieve a list of all users including only the email property.<br /><br /></p> <pre><code>GET /v1/users?select=email</code></pre>"
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Ok",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/UserCollectionDto"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "Bad request",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ApiError"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "Operations on Users"
        ],
        "summary": "Create a new user.",
        "description": "Use this call to register a new User. The UAA service will send an e-mail to the registered e-mail address with a link to confirm the e-mail address. This link includes a confirmation token as a query parameter. When the user opens the link, the frontend will use this token to perform a confirmation POST to /v1/users/confirm_email which will change the users 'confirmed' property value to true. If the 'role' property in the request body equals 'admin', authentication is required to execute this call and the authenticated user should have the role 'admin'. Therefore only admin users will be able to create new admin users.",
        "operationId": "requestPasswordResetUsingPOST",
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "OK",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/UserDto"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "Bad request",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ApiError"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "Not found",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/ApiError"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "requestBody": {
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/UserCreationDto"
              }
            }
          },
          "required": true
        }
      }
    },
