        "description": "Authenticate a user using username and password login. The response body will include a JWT (Json Web Token). Look <a href=\"https://jwt.io/introduction\">here</a> for a quick introduction to JWT. This token should be present as 'Authentication' header in all authenticated requests to the API. If the 'confirmed' property of the user is equal to 'false', an error should be thrown indicating that the user should first confirm his e-mail address. The frontend should handle this error appropriately.",
        "operationId": "acquireTokenUsingPOST",
